						<summary>

						<p>A broken slab lying the shrine of Rāma in the village.</p>						

						<p>16th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription can be assigned to the 16th century on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Broken. Records the gift of lands at Paḍadurti and renovation of certain canals and demarcated with boundaries stones containing <hi rend="italic">Vāmanamudras</hi> and given to certain Timmareḍi by Gangireḍi and • • • • • dēva mahārāja.</p>						

						</summary>
